  <h1>Inclusive Culture &amp; DE&amp;I Strategy</h1>
  <p class="project-summary">When Activision Blizzard's first EMEA DE&amp;I Manager set out to bring the company's US-centric employee networks to our region, I volunteered to lead the new Disability Network chapter. Over the following years, a team of six of us built it from a lunchtime idea into a community of around 70 members, with a programme of awareness initiatives that changed how openly our offices talked about neurodiversity, mental load and invisible disability. It is the work that shaped my "come as you are" philosophy more than anything else in my career.</p>

